layers.nm: Like branches on a tree, the nerves of the  brachial plexus split and recombine  into different sections until becoming  the terminal nerves, which are  the last major nerve branches.

s.t: Like branches on a tree, the nerves of the brachial plexus split and recombine into different sections until becoming the terminal nerves, which are the last major nerve branches.

layers.nm: Starting from the neck and moving  towards your hand, the brachial plexus  is organized into sections called  nerve roots, trunks, divisions, cords,  and terminal branches.

s.t: Starting from the neck and moving towards your hand, the brachial plexus is organized into sections called nerve roots, trunks, divisions, cords, and terminal branches.
